radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases demonstrate bibasilar atelectasis. There is no pleural effusion, focal consolidation, or pneumothorax. Multiple bilateral pulmonary nodules noted. A 4-mm nodule at the left lung base, a 4.8-mm left lower lobe nodule, and a 4.1-mm subpleural nodule in the right lower lobe. Tiny gallbladder stones noted. Dilated fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 14 mm with moderate periappendiceal inflammatory stranding and multiple reactive lymph nodes. No perforation, periappendiceal fluid collections, or abscesses.
